body:
@RvN76 thanks for your report and pull request. Did you have a look at the FAQ? 

Using a start_date of datetime.now() can lead to unpredictable behavior, and your DAG never starting. It's recommended to subtract a timespan to force the scheduler to recognize the start_date. See also http://stackoverflow.com/questions/33126159/airflow-not-scheduling-correctly-python .

And yes I agree with you that start_date is confusing...
